The Chronicle Leonard Ncube A MAN from Inyathi allegedly killed his estranged wife by stabbing her five times with a flip knife for dumping him, police confirmed on Tuesday. Police spokesperson for Matabeleland North Chief Inspector Siphiwe Makonese said the incident occurred on Friday night when Lyton Sibanda (23) of Felton Farm visited the now deceased Nontokozo Khabo (21) at her parents’ homestead in Chief Mtshane area in Inyathi. The couple had been on separation since February this year, police said. More to follow…